{# LESSON 4 #}
<div class="mb-8 mt-8 rounded-lg p-2 border border-teal-200 dark:border-teal-800 bg-teal-100 dark:bg-teal-900/20 rounded-lg">
  <h3 id="learned4" class="font-semibold">Lesson 4: Address conflict as soon as possible.</h3>
    <p class="ml-8">If conflict were to fester, the project would suffer. If anyone had issues with another team member, they could go to the producer to talk about it. The producer was responsible for assessing the conflict and helping resolve the issue. Another team member was a secondary point of contact in case the producer was involved in said conflict. Putting these systems in place helped us keep production on track.</p>
</div>

